Text.string: I don't trust strangers.
You will have to earn my respect, Vault Hunter.
How did you REALLY find us?
If you tell Maliwan our location, I will destroy you.
Typhon might be the “hero”, but I keep us alive.
Interrogate me all you want, but I will not give up Typhon's secret.
Unless you have business, leave me alone.
If it weren't for me, we would have all perished years ago.
Life isn't fun, Vault Hunter, despite what Sparrow would have you believe.
What is the point of this conversation? State your business, or go.
Now you know Typhon's secret. He is father to Tyreen and Troy.
I do not remember the children. They were gone by the time I awakened.
The first thing I remember Typhon saying to me is, “You must help me survive.”
He is gone. But we will remember him.
After Typhon's death, it will take some time for Sparrow to return to his previous average output: fifty-three percent. On a good day.
Once we purge Maliwan, the planet will be ours.
Don't worry about us. We will be fine on our own.
Now it's up to us to survive.
And then there were two...
How does it feel to be a hero?
Typhon... would be proud of you.
I am surprised you saved the galaxy. But I am... glad I am surprised.
We are the caretakers of this planet, now.
Typhon entered this galaxy a human and became a star. Not many can say that, I suppose.
Please do not invade my personal space, or I will destroy you.
If you have a survival query, come to me. If you wish to “party down”, talk to Sparrow.
I can smell the death on you.
This is a strange planet, is it not?
It's dangerous to go alone. That is the purpose of “friendship”: survival.
If you tell Maliwan of the Machine, I will destroy you.
If you tell anyone Typhon's secret, I will destroy you.
He is gone.
Ah, the hero of the galaxy graces us.
[humming]||—Ngh. Music. What is the point?
Sparrow! What are you doing!
Get back to work, Sparrow!
Where did my Eridium go?
I am safe... for now.
You have unfinished business.
Do the thing I asked you to.
If you don't complete your mission, we will all perish.
Oh, greetings.
Yes, I see you.
State your business.
Thought you could sneak up on me, did you? I mean... Hello.
You're not dead... How curious.
Good day, Vault Hunter. Though what constitutes a good day anyway?
Do you hate the day as much as I do, Vault Hunter?
Oh, it's just the Vault Hunter. Nighttime is pointless.
I barely spotted you there. I hate nighttime.
You will work for me.
I have a job for you.
You're not busy. Lend a hand.
I will give your life purpose.
Your skills are required.
Don't forget your task.
You have business to finish.
Finish what you promised.
Do what is required of you.
You must continue your quest.
Until next time.
Don't die.
Try to survive.
Goodbye for now.
I have important business to attend to.
Finally.
That took long enough.
And back to work.
Now, what was I doing?
And I am alone.
